Elsewhere at Flushing Meadows, few tears will have been shed for Wayne Odesnik after he lost in straight sets on Tuesday to Kei Nishikori.

The US Tennis Association had been forced to give the controversial American a wildcard by virtue of him being the best performer at a series of Challenger events. It was done with reluctance as he was banned for owning Human Growth Hormone in 2010.

