Brits are thin on the ground in singles but outstanding 17-year-old Borna Coric is a good proxy.

The longtime Middlesex-based Croatian, who is coached by Englishman Ryan Jones, caused a significant upset on Tuesday when he thrashed 29th seed Lukas Rosol 6-4, 6-1, 6-2 having come through qualifying.

The reigning US Open junior champion, he is a name to remember. 

